quran[13]{c,v,t}:
  27,23,"I found a woman ruling over them, and she has been given everything and has a splendid throne"
  27,24,"I found both her and her people bowing down on their knees to the sun instead of to God [Alone]. Satan has made their actions seem attractive to them, and diverted them from the [proper] Way. They are not guided"
  27,25,"so they do not bow down on their knees before God, Who brings forth what is concealed in Heaven and Earth, and knows anything you hide as well as anything you display"
  27,26,"God, there is no deity except Him, Lord of the splendid Throne"
  27,27,"He said: \"We shall see whether you have been truthful or are a liar"
  27,28,"Take this letter of mine and deliver it to them. Then leave them, and see what [answer] they send back"
  27,29,"She said: \"Councilmen, an important letter has been delivered to me"
  27,30,"It is from Solomon and it (reads]: \"In the name of God, the Mercy-giving, the Merciful"
  27,31,"Do not act haughtily towards me, and come to me committed to [live at] peace"
  27,32,"She said: \"Councilmen, give me your opinion concerning my affair: I have never settled any matter unless you were present with me"
  27,33,"They said: \"We possess strength and can be extremely violent, while authority rests with you; so attend to whatever you will command"
  27,34,"She said: Â´Whenever any kings enter a town and plunder it, they turn the most important men among its people into the lowest. Thus they act"
  27,35,I am sending them a gift and shall be watching for whatever the emissaries bring back